# Byte-compiled / optimized / DLL files
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]

# PyCharm artifacts
.idea/

# Environment directories (commonly used names for virtual environments)
.env
.venv/
env/
venv/

# OSX
.DS_Store

# Logs
*.log
Explanation:

__pycache__/ and *.py[cod]: Python generates bytecode files that shouldn't be in the repository.

.idea/: If you're using PyCharm, it creates this directory for project-specific settings.

.env, .venv/, env/, venv/: Common directories for Python virtual environments.

.DS_Store: A file macOS creates in every directory.

*.log: Log files.

This should cover most of the basics for a beginner's project. As you expand your toolset or the complexity of your project, you can always adjust and expand your .gitignore file accordingly.





